<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376792>
    dc:description "Figs 1–10. Adult Stamnodes Guenée, [1858], dorsal (a) and ventral (b) views. 1. S. aumatlapalli sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (USNMENT01523813). 2. S. cannonaria (Schaus, 1927), holotype, ♂ (USNMENT01771251), photo credit NMNH type search (https://collections.nmnh.si.edu/search/ento/). 3. S. penguinifera (Dyar, 1910) (USNMENT01521263). 4. S. clara sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (AMNH_IZC 00353930).5.S.?claraaberration (EMEC1748437).6. S. carotasp. nov.,holotype, ♀(BMEC). 7. S.favilla sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (USNMENT00868520). 8. S. fuego sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (USNMENT01771229). 9. S. matrona sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (EMEC1748430). 10. S. splendorata Pearsall, 1909 (DLW). Scale bar = 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376792/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376805>
    dc:description "Figs 44–46. Male genitalia: genital capsules (a) and phalli (b). 44. S. clara sp. nov., holotype (TAM- 2022-130, AMNH). 45. S. carota sp. nov., paratype (TAM-2023-262, USNM 154208). 46. S. favilla sp. nov., paratype (TAM-2020-042, CNIN). Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376805/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376821>
    dc:description "Figs 61–63. Female genitalia. 61. S. aumatlapalli sp. nov., paratype (TAM-2020-041, CNIN). 62. S. penguinifera (Dyar, 1910) (TAM-2023-249, CMNH). 63. S. carota sp. nov., holotype (TAM- 2023-263, BMEC). Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376821/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376829>
    dc:description "Figs 74–81. Distributions of newly described Stamnodes Guenée, [1858]. 74. S. aumatlapalli sp. nov. 75. S. clara sp. nov. 76. S. carota sp. nov. 77. S. favilla sp. nov. 78. S. fuego sp. nov. 79. S. matrona sp. nov. 80. S. disrupta sp. nov. 81. S. mariachi sp. nov. Single dots may represent>1 individual. Scale bars = 400 km." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376829/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376837>
    dc:description "Fig. 95. Biogeographic associations of Mexican Stamnodes Guenée, [1858]. (*) denotes species found in two or more provinces. Underlying biogeographic provincial map taken from Morrone (2020: fig. 4.5) with permission to reproduce this figure granted by author Juan J. Morrone." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376837/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

